## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="6a5e0-103">将 <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> 特性应用于某个类型，以指示此类型的实例可以被序列化。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6a5e0-103">Apply the <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> attribute to a type to indicate that instances of this type can be serialized.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6a5e0-104">公共语言运行时会引发<xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationException>任何一种关系图中要序列化的对象没有<xref:System.SerializableAttribute>应用的属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6a5e0-104">The common language runtime throws <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationException> if any type in the graph of objects being serialized does not have the <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> attribute applied.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="6a5e0-105">应用<xref:System.SerializableAttribute>属性即使类还实现<xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.ISerializable>接口来控制序列化过程。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6a5e0-105">Apply the <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> attribute even if the class also implements the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.ISerializable> interface to control the serialization process.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="6a5e0-106">当你将<xref:System.SerializableAttribute>属性到一个类型，专用和公用的所有字段进行序列都化默认情况下。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6a5e0-106">When you apply the <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> attribute to a type, all private and public fields are serialized by default.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6a5e0-107">你可以通过实现更精细地控制序列化<xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.ISerializable>接口来重写序列化过程。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6a5e0-107">You can control serialization more granularly by implementing the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.ISerializable> interface to override the serialization process.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="6a5e0-108">你可以通过应用排除从序列化的字段或<xref:System.NonSerializedAttribute>属性字段。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6a5e0-108">Or you can exclude fields from serialization by applying the <xref:System.NonSerializedAttribute> attribute to the field.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6a5e0-109">如果可序列化类型的字段包含一个指针、 句柄或某些其他数据结构，它是特定于特定的环境，并且不能有意义的方式重建在不同环境中，则你可能想要应用<xref:System.NonSerializedAttribute>属性给该字段。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6a5e0-109">If a field of a serializable type contains a pointer, a handle, or some other data structure that is specific to a particular environment, and cannot be meaningfully reconstituted in a different environment, then you might want to apply the <xref:System.NonSerializedAttribute> attribute to that field.</span></span>  
  
